<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2651</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the French Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DCC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chambrun</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-24">December
                                    24, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of a Note from the French Ambassador, dated November 12, 1918,
                            advising that the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the French Republic
                            states that the delegate of the Polish National Committee at Paris,
                            recognized by the Allies, has applied to him for permission to
                            participate in the peace conference when questions bearing upon Polish
                            affairs are taken up, and requesting to be informed as to the sentiment
                            of the United States government on the subject.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to say that as soon as the position of the
                            United States on this question is determined you will be promptly
                            informed.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>